#  Solution

Context()->texStrings;
SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR
$BBOLD  SOLUTION $EBOLD
$PAR
The graphs of both \( f(x) = 3^x \ \) and \( \ f(x) = 3^{-x} \ \)
have the same horizontal asymptote. Their asymptote is the \(x\)-axis,
whose equation is \( y=0 \). The graph of \( y=\log_3{x} \) is asymptotic
to the \(y\)-axis, hence the equation of its asymptote is \( x=0 \).

END_SOLUTION
